The paper discusses the use of machine learning for procedural level generation in games, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the interaction between human designers and the PLGML agent, which involves aspects of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The study also involves user testing, which could fall under the category of graphics (cs.GR) or machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses the comparative study of different PLGML approaches, which could fall under the category of software engineering (cs.SE) or systems and control (cs.SY).
